Faulty air inlet, because the oven bag wasn’t fully filled with air. Therefore, it is possible that unfiltered air was sucked from the environmnent.

Due to an interruption because of rain the tenax tube was adjusted to the pump, but the oven bag couldn’t be placed. Therefore the tube (open on one side, was placed under the cover and the whole setup was installed 1h later than the samples.
Before baking the bag was already taken once to the field, but wasn’t used. Therefore it could be more contaminated then the bags of the samples.
